  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large bowl, mix together millet flour, water, mustard seeds, ginger, garlic powder, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Knead the mixture for 10 minutes to develop the gluten.",
    "Divide the dough into 8-10 equal pieces.",
    "Roll each piece into a ball and then flatten it slightly into a disk shape.",
    "Heat a non-stick skillet over medium-high heat and cook the injera pieces for 2-3 minutes on each side.",
    "Transfer the injera to a baking sheet and bake for 10-12 minutes.",
    "Meanwhile, mix together chimichurri sauce, candy cane sugar, and chopped parsley in a small bowl.",
    "Serve the warm injera pieces with the mustardy sauce spooned over the top."
